parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle hesitates to stop
or the brakes fail to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
or the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
or the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags do not deploy to cushion the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
airbag light comes on
passenger airbag lifts up from the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal is slow to respond
brake pedal is difficult to depress
brake failure without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause unexpected and unpredictable behavior of the vehicle's systems, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Horn sounds without warning
horn does not sound when pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the Goodyear Eagle RSA tire can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tire blowout
sidewall separation from the tread
sudden loss of air pressure
loss of control
and potential damage to the wheel rim.
